Description

                            Presentations by Power Point to Group of Students and at Schools and Colleges to create Knowledge Building on CSR and Social Activities to Empower Greater Employability amongst Rural Young Minds;  
Prepare Village Level Team of Young Minds on Linked up Goals for ease Implementation; 
Organise Village Level Discussion Sessions on UN Sustainable Development Goals-2030 and Sharing Success Stories; for UN SDGs-2030 Action Formula.   
Organise Competitions on Importance of UN SDGs-2030 and Recognising Best Rural Young Mind of Sustainable Development. ;  
Preparing a Database of Who's Who of Young Minds on UN SDG-2030;

Expected impact

                            Creating  wider awareness on UN SDGs-2030 and their Benefits to Humanity, Family, Societies, Villages, Cities, States, Countries are very important and promoting the same through our Young Minds shall be a long tern Action Strategic Programme , including Student Exchange Programmes on UN SDGs-2030..  Under CSR Wing, joining hands with Philanthropists, Mentors and Teachers, Social Entrepreneurs, NGOs, MNCs, sett-up Model  Centres on UN SDGs-2030 along with Skill Development Programmes.

Website

                            www.rrrindustries.com; www.mimsglobaledu.org

Description

                            1. Project goals: The project aims to achieve the following goals: 
â— Raise young people, especially high school studentsâ€™ awareness about social problems through 17 SDGs; 
â— Encourage them to involve in social responsibilities, especially to take the vital role of the youth in implementing SDGs by 2030 in Vietnam;
â— Support them to take actions to put their ideas for community into practice; 
â— Empower their potential and leadership skills by YSEALIâ€™s vision, mission, engaging activities and inspiring communities; 
â— Raise awareness of young people in Vinh Yen Highschool in particular and Vinh Phuc Province in general about ASEAN Community. 

2. Objectives: 
â— Recruit 10 volunteers who are local youth such as college students in Vinh Phuc province and 10 volunteers from 2030 Youth Force Vietnam network to help the projects both all stages and future projects;
â— Train about 17 SDGs for 840 students at Vinh Yen Highschool through information day, training workshops and a contest; 
â— Raise the awareness and the emotion of students for ASEAN Community through a solidarity song related to ASEAN; 
â— Support at least 06 ideas of these students to apply the ideas or initiatives at Vinh Yen Highschool after the contest to create sustainable school environment in the countryside; 
â— Partner with Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union at Vinh Yen Highschool to invite other Student Ambassadors from other High schools nearby to join the Information Day

Expected impact

                            - Direct beneficiaries:
+ 840 students at Vinh Yen Highschool joining the SDGs Bootcamp; 
+ 10 young volunteers in the northern region of 2030 Youth Force Vietnam network involving in the project; 
 + At least 6 ideas will be put into practice to create sustainable school at Vinh Yen Highschool; 
+ 10 local volunteers involving in the project. 

- Indirect beneficiaries: 
840 studentsâ€™ families and relatives at local community, especially at Hoi Hop Ward;
Teachers and school's staffs at Vinh Yen Highschool.

